Name: Toomes
Line: Things are never gonna be the same now. I mean, look at this. You got aliens. You got big green guys tearing down buildings. When I was a kid, I used to draw cowboys and Indians.

Name: Mason
Line: Actually, it's Native American, but whatever.

Name: Toomes
Line: Yeah. Tell you what, though. It ain't bad, is it?

Name: Mason
Line: No. Yeah. Kid's got a future.

Name: Toomes
Line: Yeah, well... We'll see, I guess.

Name: Toomes
Line: No, hey! Uh-uh! You can't saw through that stuff. These alien bastards are tough. You gotta use the stuff they use.

Name: Toomes
Line: See?

Name: Schultz
Line: All right.

Name: Toomes
Line: All right. (to Brice) Oh, hey! Glad you could join us. Afternoon.

Name: Brice
Line: Yeah. My alarm didn't go off.

Name: Toomes
Line: Yeah, yeah, yeah, your alarm. Look, just go stack that armor plating like I asked you. This is a huge deal for us.

Name: Toomes
Line: Who the hell are you?

Name: Toomes
Line: Look, I have a city contract to salvage all this, okay, with the city, so-

Name: Toomes
Line: Ma'am, what am I- Please. Come here. Hey, lady, come on. Look... I bought trucks for this job. I brought in a whole new crew. These guys have a family. I have a family. I'm all in on this. I could lose my house.

Name: Toomes
Line: What'd you say?

Name: Toomes
Line: Yeah, he's right. I overextended myself.

Name: Toomes
Line: Your superiors. Who the hell are they?

Name: Schultz
Line: So now the assholes who made this mess are being paid to clean it up.

Name: Mason
Line: Yeah, it’s all rigged.

Name: Brice
Line: I ain’t hauling it.

Name: Mason
Line: It’s too bad. We could have made some pretty cool stuff from all that alien junk.

Name: Toomes
Line: I tell you what, let’s keep it. The world’s changing.

Name: Toomes
Line: It’s time we change, too.

Name: Toomes
Line: There you go, Mason.

Name: Toomes
Line: Business is good.

Name: Peter
Line: (in a gravelly voice) New York. Queens. It’s a rough borough, but hey, it’s home.

Name: Happy
Line: Who are you talking to?

Name: Peter
Line: (in a normal voice) No one. Just making a little video of the trip.

Name: Happy
Line: You know you can’t show it to anyone.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, I know.

Name: Happy
Line: Then why are you narrating in that voice?

Name: Peter
Line: Uh... Because it’s fun.

Name: Happy
Line: Fun.

Name: Peter
Line: So, uh, why do they call you Happy?

Name: Happy
Line: Come on. I’m not carrying your bags. Let’s go.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, should I go to the bathroom before?

Name: Happy
Line: There’s a bathroom on it.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa. No pilot? That’s awesome.

Name: Happy
Line: Is that where you’re gonna sit?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah.

Name: Happy
Line: This is your first time on a private plane?

Name: Peter
Line: My first time on any plane.

Name: Peter
Line: Should it...? Should it be...? Should it be making that noise?

Name: Peter
Line: Shh.

Name: Peter
Line: No one has actually told me why I’m in Berlin or what I’m doing. Something about Captain America going crazy.

Name: Happy
Line: (pointing at a door) This is you.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, we’re neighbors?

Name: Happy
Line: We’re not roommates. Suit up.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay, Peter, you got this. You got this.

Name: Happy
Line: What the hell are you wearing?

Name: Peter
Line: It’s my suit.

Name: Happy
Line: Where’s the case?

Name: Peter
Line: What case? That’s not my...

Name: Peter
Line: What? I thought that was a closet. This is still my room?

Name: Happy
Line: Go. Please.

Name: Peter
Line: My room is way bigger than...

Name: Happy
Line: There.

Name: Peter
Line: I found the case. I found the case. I found the case.

Name: Peter
Line: “A minor upgrade”?

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa. Oh my God.

Name: Happy
Line: Put it on.

Name: Peter
Line: What the...? This is the coolest thing I’ve ever seen-

Name: Happy
Line: Let’s go.

Name: Peter
Line: But, yeah. Well, I don’t understand. Is it for me?

Name: Peter
Line: Happy, Happy, wait.

Name: Peter
Line: This is insane. Insane. Look at this thing. Look. Look at the eyes. This is the greatest day of my life.

Name: Happy
Line: Let’s go.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay.

Name: Happy
Line: Come on.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) Okay, there’s Captain America, Iron Man, Black Widow. Whoa. Who’s that new guy?

Name: Tony
Line: Underoos!

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, that’s me. I gotta go. I gotta go.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, everyone.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay, so the craziest thing just happened, right? I just had a fight with Captain America and I stole his shield and I threw it at him-

Name: Peter
Line: What the hell? He’s big now. I gotta go. Hang on.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa!

Name: Peter
Line: It was the most amazing thing that’s ever happened! So Mr. Stark was like, “Hey, Underoos!” and I just sort of flipped in and I stole Cap’s shield. I was like, “Hey, what’s up, everybody?” And then...

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, just a second! Coming!

Name: Peter
Line: Hey.

Name: Happy
Line: We have thin walls here.

Name: Tony
Line: What are you doing, a little video diary?

Name: Peter
Line: (embarrassed) Yeah.

Name: Tony
Line: It’s all right. I’d probably do the same.

Name: Happy
Line: (from the driver’s seat) I told him not to do it. He was filming everything.

Name: Tony
Line: It’s okay.

Name: Happy
Line: I’m gonna wipe the chip.

Name: Tony
Line: Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey. You know what? We should actually... We should make an alibi video for your aunt anyway. You ready?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, hold on.

Name: Tony
Line: We rolling?

Name: Peter
Line: An alibi? Sure.

Name: Tony
Line: Get in the frame.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay.

Name: Tony
Line: Hey, May. How you doing? What are you wearing? Something skimpy, I hope.

Name: Tony
Line: Peter, that’s inappropriate. All right, let’s start over. You can edit it.

Name: Peter
Line: Mm-hmm.

Name: Tony
Line: Three, two, one. Hey, May. My gosh, uh, I wanted to tell you what an incredible job your nephew did this weekend at the Stark internship retreat. Everyone was impressed.

Name: Happy
Line: Come on! It’s a freaking merge. (to Tony) I’m sorry.

Name: Tony
Line: This is because you’re not on Queens Boulevard. (to the camera) See, Happy is... is hoping to get bumped up to asset management. He was forehead of security, and before that, he was just a driver.

Name: Happy
Line: That was a private conversation. I don’t like joking about this. It was hard for me to talk to you about that.

Name: Tony
Line: No, seriously, was he snoring a bunch?

Name: Happy
Line: All right. Here we are. End of the line. Whoops.

Name: Tony
Line: Happy, can you give us a moment?

Name: Happy
Line: You want me to leave the car?

Name: Tony
Line: Why don’t you grab Peter’s case out of the trunk.

Name: Peter
Line: I can keep the suit?

Name: Tony
Line: Yes, we were just talking about it.

Name: Tony
Line: Do me a favor, though. Happy’s kind of your point guy on this. Don’t stress him out. Don’t do anything stupid. I’ve seen his cardiogram. All right?

Name: Peter
Line: (enthusiastically) Yes.

Name: Tony
Line: Don’t do anything I would do, and definitely don’t do anything I wouldn’t do. There’s a... There’s a little grey area in there, and that’s where you operate.

Name: Peter
Line: Wait, does that mean that I’m an Avenger?

Name: Tony
Line: No.

Name: Happy
Line: This it?

Name: Tony
Line: Seventh floor.

Name: Peter
Line: I can take that. You don’t have to take it.

Name: Happy
Line: You’re gonna take it?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, I can take that.

Name: Happy
Line: Thank you.

Name: Peter
Line: So when’s, when’s our next... When’s our next “retreat,” you know? Like...

Name: Tony
Line: What, next mission?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, the mission. The missions.

Name: Tony
Line: We’ll call you.

Name: Peter
Line: Do you have my numbers?

Name: Tony
Line: No, I mean, we’ll call you. Like, someone will call you.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh.

Name: Tony
Line: All right?

Name: Peter
Line: From your team.

Name: Tony
Line: Okay.

Name: Tony
Line: It’s not a hug. I’m just grabbing the door for you. We’re not there yet.

Name: Tony
Line: Bye.

Name: Peter
Line: They’re gonna call me.

Name: Flash
Line: What’s up, Penis Parker?

Name: Ned
Line: (imitating Emperor Palpatine) Join me, and together... we’ll build my new Lego Death Star.

Name: Peter
Line: What?

Name: Peter
Line: No way! That’s awesome. How many pieces?

Name: Ned
Line: Three thousand eight hundred and three.

Name: Peter
Line: That’s insane.

Name: Ned
Line: I know. You want to build it tonight?

Name: Peter
Line: No, I can’t tonight. I’ve got the Stark-

Name: Ned
Line: Mm-hmm. Stark internship.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, exactly.

Name: Ned
Line: Always got that internship.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, well, hopefully, soon it’ll lead to a real job with them.

Name: Ned
Line: That would be so sweet.

Name: Peter
Line: Right?

Name: Ned
Line: He’d be all, “Good job on those spreadsheets, Peter. Here’s a gold coin.”

Name: Ned
Line: I don’t know how jobs work.

Name: Peter
Line: That’s exactly how they work.

Name: Ned
Line: Oh. (chuckles) I’ll knock out the basic bones of the Death Star at my place. And, and then I’ll come by afterwards...

Name: Ned
Line: ...because for the most part, the difficult thing is the base of it. The top half we can knock out in two hours, tops.

Name: Peter
Line: That’d be great.

Name: Flash
Line: It’s the product of sine of the angle and gravity divided by the mass.

Name: Peter
Line: Uh... Uh... Yeah, yeah.

Name: Peter
Line: Uh... Mass cancels out, so it’s just gravity times sine.

Name: Flash
Line: (whispers) You’re dead.

Name: Peter
Line: Did Liz get a new top?

Name: Ned
Line: No. We’ve seen that before, but never with that skirt.

Name: Liz
Line: Hi!

Name: Peter
Line: We should probably stop staring before it gets creepy, though.

Name: Michelle
Line: Too late.

Name: Michelle
Line: You guys are losers.

Name: Ned
Line: But then why do you sit with us?

Name: Michelle
Line: Because I don’t have any friends.

Name: Liz
Line: Let’s move to the next question. What is the heaviest naturally-occurring element?

Name: Liz
Line: That is correct. Thank you, Abraham.

Name: Liz
Line: Please open your books to page ten.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Peter, it’s nationals. Is there no way you could take one weekend off?

Name: Peter
Line: I can’t go to Washington because if Mr. Stark needs me, then I have to make sure that I’m here.

Name: Flash
Line: You’ve never even been in the same room as Tony Stark.

Name: Liz
Line: Really? Right before nationals?

Name: Michelle
Line: He already quit marching band and robotics lab.

Name: Michelle
Line: I’m not obsessed with him. Just very observant.

Name: Liz
Line: Flash, you’re in for Peter.

Name: Flash
Line: Ooh, I don’t know. I gotta check my calendar first. I got a hot date with Black Widow coming up.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: What did I tell you about using the bell for comedic purposes?

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, what’s up?

Name: Peter
Line: What’s up, Mr. Delmar?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, um, and, uh, with pickles, and can you smush it down real flat? Thanks.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, she’s alright.

Name: Peter
Line: ¿Cómo está tu hija, eh? (How is your daughter, huh?)

Name: Peter
Line: It’s five dollars.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, come on, I’m joking. I’m joking.

Name: Peter
Line: Here’s five dollars.

Name: Peter
Line: What’s up, Murph? How you doing, buddy?

Name: Peter
Line: Ah, you know, it’s boring. Got better things to do.

Name: Peter
Line: This is great.

Name: Peter
Line: Ah, finally.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, could you hold this for a second? Thanks.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, is this anybody’s bike? No?

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, buddy, is this your bike?

Name: Peter
Line: Does anyone have a pen? Do you have a pen?

Name: Peter
Line: Whoo! Everybody good?

Name: Peter
Line: Call me Spider-Man!

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, buddy. Shouldn’t steal cars. It’s bad.

Name: Peter
Line: I was just tryin’ to-

Name: Peter
Line: How was I supposed to know? He was putting that thing in the window!

Name: Peter
Line: Ugh! I’m good, I’m good.

Name: Happy
Line: Happy Hogan.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Happy! Um, here’s my report for tonight. I stopped a grand theft bicycle. Couldn’t find the owner, so I just left a note. Um... I helped this lost, old Dominican lady. She was really nice and bought me a churro. So I just, um, feel like I could be doing more. You know? Just curious when the next real mission is gonna be. So, yeah, just call me back. It’s Peter. Parker.

Name: Peter
Line: Why would I tell him about the churro?

Name: Peter
Line: Finally, something good.

Name: Peter
Line: (clears his throat) What’s up, guys? You forgot your PIN number?

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa! You’re the Avengers. What are you guys doing here?

Name: Peter
Line: Thor. Hulk. Good to finally meet you guys. I thought you’d be more handsome in person.

Name: Peter
Line: Iron Man. Hey, what are you doing robbing a bank? You’re a billionaire.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey! Oh, this feels so weird.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, what is that thing?

Name: Peter
Line: I’m starting... to think... you’re not... the Avengers!

Name: Peter
Line: Alright guys, let’s wrap this up. It’s a school night.

Name: Peter
Line: So, how do jerks like you get tech like this?

Name: Peter
Line: No. Wait, wait, wait!

Name: Peter
Line: Mr. Delmar.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Mr. Delmar, you in there? Is anybody in here? Hello?

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, come on. You’ve got to be-

Name: Peter
Line: Here, here.

Name: Happy
Line: (to Dum-E) Okay. Good. Yes. Yes- No. No, put that down. That’s worth more than you or me. (takes a call) Yeah?

Name: Peter
Line: Happy, the craziest thing just happened to me. These guys were robbing an ATM with these high tech weapons-

Name: Happy
Line: Hey, take a breath, okay? I don’t have time for ATM robberies...

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, but-

Name: Happy
Line: ...or the thoughtful notes you leave behind. I have moving day to worry about. Everything’s gotta be out of here by next week.

Name: Peter
Line: Wait. Wait! You’re moving? Who’s moving?

Name: Happy
Line: Yeah, don’t you watch the news? Tony sold Avengers Tower. We’re relocating to a new facility upstate where, hopefully, the cell service is much worse.

Name: Peter
Line: But what about me?

Name: Happy
Line: What about you?

Name: Peter
Line: Well, what if Mr. Stark needs me or something, I don’t know, something big goes down? Can I please just talk to Mr. Stark?

Name: Happy
Line: Look, just stay away from anything too dangerous. I’m responsible for making sure you’re responsible, okay?

Name: Peter
Line: I am responsible. I- Oh, crap. My backpack’s gone.

Name: Happy
Line: That doesn’t sound responsible.

Name: Peter
Line: I’ll call you back.

Name: Happy
Line: Feel free not to.

Name: May
Line: What was that?

Name: Peter
Line: Uh, it’s nothing. It’s nothing!

Name: Ned
Line: You’re the Spider-Man. From YouTube.

Name: Peter
Line: I’m not. I’m not.

Name: Ned
Line: You were on the ceiling.

Name: Peter
Line: No, I wasn’t. Ned, what are you doing in my room?

Name: Ned
Line: May let me in. You said we were gonna finish the Death Star.

Name: Peter
Line: You can’t just bust into my room!

Name: May
Line: The turkey meatloaf recipe is a disaster. Let’s go to dinner. Thai? Ned, you want Thai?

Name: Ned
Line: Yes.

Name: Peter
Line: No. He’s got a thing.

Name: Ned
Line: A thing to do after.

Name: May
Line: Okay.

Name: May
Line: Maybe put on some clothes.

Name: Ned
Line: Oh, she doesn’t know?

Name: Peter
Line: Nobody knows. I mean, Mr. Stark knows because he made my suit, but that’s it.

Name: Ned
Line: (whispers) Tony Stark made you that? Are you an Avenger?

Name: Peter
Line: (hesitates) Yeah, basically.

Name: Ned
Line: Whoa...

Name: Peter
Line: You can’t tell anybody about this. You gotta keep it a secret.

Name: Ned
Line: A secret? Why?

Name: Peter
Line: You know what she’s like. If she finds out people try and kill me every single night, she’s not going to let me do this anymore. Come on, Ned, please.

Name: Ned
Line: Okay, okay, okay, okay, okay, okay. I’ll level with you. I don’t think I can keep this a secret. This is the greatest thing that’s ever happened to me, Peter!

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, May cannot know. I cannot do that to her right now, you know? I mean, everything that’s happened with her, I... Please.

Name: Ned
Line: Okay.

Name: Peter
Line: Just swear it, okay?

Name: Ned
Line: I swear.

Name: Peter
Line: Thank you.

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah.

Name: Peter
Line: I can’t believe this is happening right now.

Name: Ned
Line: Can I try the suit on?

Name: Peter
Line: No.

Name: Ned
Line: How does it work? Is it magnets? How do you shoot the strings?

Name: Peter
Line: I’m gonna tell you about this at school tomorrow, okay?

Name: Ned
Line: Great. Okay, well, wait, then. How do you do this and the Stark internship?

Name: Peter
Line: This is the Stark internship.

Name: Ned
Line: Oh.

Name: Peter
Line: Just get out of here.

Name: May
Line: What’s the matter? Thought you loved larb. It’s too larby? Not larby enough. How many times do I have to say “larb” before you talk to me? You know I larb you.

Name: Peter
Line: I’m just stressed. The internship, and I’m tired. A lot of work.

Name: May
Line: The Stark internship. I have to tell you, not a fan of that Tony Stark. Distracted all the time... he’s got you in your head.

Name: May
Line: What does he have you doing?

Name: May
Line: You need to use your instincts.

Name: May
Line: If you spot something like that happening, you turn and you run the other way.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah. Of course.

Name: May
Line: Six blocks away from us.

Name: Peter
Line: I... uh... I need a new backpack.

Name: May
Line: What?

Name: Peter
Line: I need a new backpack.

Name: May
Line: That’s five.

Name: May
Line: Oh, we didn’t order that.

Name: May
Line: Oh! Thanks. (to Peter) That’s nice of him.

Name: Peter
Line: I think he larbs you.

Name: Ned
Line: You got bit by a spider? Can it bite me? Well, it probably would’ve hurt, right? You know what? Whatever. Even if it did hurt, I’d let it bite me. Maybe. How much did it hurt?

Name: Peter
Line: The spider’s dead, Ned.

Name: Ned
Line: Whoa.

Name: Ned
Line: You were here?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah.

Name: Ned
Line: You could’ve died.

Name: Ned
Line: Do you lay eggs?

Name: Peter
Line: What? No.

Name: Ned
Line: (in a low voice) Can you spit venom?

Name: Peter
Line: No.

Name: Ned
Line: Can you summon an army of spiders?

Name: Peter
Line: No, Ned.

Name: Ned
Line: How far can you shoot your webs?

Name: Peter
Line: It’s unknown. Shut up.

Name: Ned
Line: If I was you, I would stand on the edge of a building and just shoot it as far as I could-

Name: Peter
Line: Shut up, Ned.

Name: Ned
Line: Do you know him too?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, we met.

Name: Peter
Line: I stole his shield.

Name: Ned
Line: What?

Name: Ned
Line: Do Avengers have to pay taxes?

Name: Peter
Line: Shh!

Name: Ned
Line: What does Hulk smell like?

Name: Peter
Line: Shh!

Name: Ned
Line: I bet he smells nice.

Name: Peter
Line: You have to shut up.

Name: Ned
Line: Is Captain America cool, or is he like a mean, old grandpa?

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, just, shh, okay?

Name: Ned
Line: Hey, can I be your guy in the chair?

Name: Peter
Line: What?

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah. You know how there’s a guy with a headset telling the other guy where to go?

Name: Ned
Line: Like, like if you’re stuck in a burning building, I could tell you where to go. Because there’d be screens around me, and I could, you know, swivel around, and... ‘Cause I could be your guy in the chair.

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, I don’t need a guy in the chair.

Name: Liz
Line: Did you guys see the bank security cam on YouTube? He fought off four guys.

Name: Liz
Line: (shrugs) Kind of?

Name: Liz
Line: I wouldn’t care. I would still love him for the person he is on the inside.

Name: Ned
Line: (in a loud voice) Peter knows Spider-Man!

Name: Peter
Line: (stuttering) No, I don’t. No. I... I mean...

Name: Ned
Line: They’re friends.

Name: Flash
Line: Yeah, like Coach Wilson and Captain America are friends.

Name: Peter
Line: (stuttering) I’ve met him. Yeah. A couple times. But it’s, um... through the Stark internship. Mm-hmm.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, well. I’m not really supposed to talk about it.

Name: Flash
Line: Well, that’s awesome. Hey, you know what? Maybe you should invite him to Liz’s party. Right?

Name: Liz
Line: Yeah, I’m having people over tonight. You’re more than welcome to come.

Name: Peter
Line: Having a party?

Name: Flash
Line: Yeah, it’s gonna be dope. You should totally invite your personal friend Spider-Man.

Name: Peter
Line: Um...

Name: Liz
Line: It’s okay. I know Peter’s way too busy for parties anyway, so...

Name: Flash
Line: Come on. He’ll be there. Right, Parker?

Name: Peter
Line: What are you doing?

Name: Ned
Line: (in a hushed voice) Helping you out. Did you not hear her? Liz has a crush on you.

Name: Ned
Line: Dude, you’re an Avenger. If any one of us has a chance with a senior girl, it’s you.

Name: May
Line: House party in the suburbs. Oh, I remember these. Kind of jealous.

Name: Ned
Line: It’ll be a night to remember.

Name: May
Line: (laughs) Ned, some hats wear men. You wear that hat.

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah, it gives me confidence.

Name: May
Line: Hmm.

Name: Peter
Line: This is a mistake. (to May) Hey, let’s just go home.

Name: May
Line: Oh, Peter. I know. I know it’s really hard trying to fit in with all the changes your body’s going through. It’s flowering now.

Name: Peter
Line: Uh-huh.

Name: May
Line: (to Ned) He’s so stressed out lately.

Name: Ned
Line: What helps with stress is going to a party. We should go to the party.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, let’s do it. Yeah. I’m gonna go. I’m gonna go.

Name: May
Line: Peter.

Name: May
Line: Have fun, okay?

Name: Peter
Line: (nods) I will.

Name: May
Line: (in a soft voice) Okay.

Name: Ned
Line: Bye, May!

Name: Ned
Line: Dude, you have the suit, right?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah.

Name: Ned
Line: This is gonna change our lives.

Name: Ned
Line: Okay. We’re gonna have Spider-Man swing in, say you guys are tight, and then I get a fist bump or one of those half bro-hugs.

Name: Michelle
Line: Can’t believe you guys are at this lame party.

Name: Ned
Line: But you’re here too.

Name: Michelle
Line: Am I?

Name: Liz
Line: Oh, my gosh.

Name: Liz
Line: Hey, guys. Cool hat, Ned.

Name: Ned
Line: Hi, Liz.

Name: Peter
Line: Hi, Liz.

Name: Liz
Line: I’m so happy you guys came. There’s pizza and drinks. Help yourself.

Name: Peter
Line: What a great party.

Name: Liz
Line: Thanks.

Name: Liz
Line: (sheepish) Oh, I... My parents will kill me if anything’s broken. I gotta-

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah.

Name: Liz
Line: Have fun.

Name: Ned
Line: Bye.

Name: Liz
Line: Bye.

Name: Ned
Line: Dude, what are you doing? She’s here. Spider it up.

Name: Peter
Line: No, no, no. I can’t... I cannot do this. Spider-Man is not a party trick, okay? Look, I’m just gonna... be myself.

Name: Ned
Line: (sighs) Peter, no one wants that.

Name: Peter
Line: Dude.

Name: Flash
Line: (into a microphone) Penis Parker, what’s up?

Name: Flash
Line: So, where’s your pal Spider-Man? Let me guess. In Canada with your imaginary girlfriend?

Name: Flash
Line: That’s not Spider-Man. That’s just Ned in a red shirt.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, what’s up? I’m Spider-Man. Just thought I’d swing by and say hello to my buddy Peter. Oh, what’s up, Ned? Hey, where’s Peter, anyways? He must be around...

Name: Peter
Line: God, this is stupid. What am I doing?

Name: Peter
Line: What the hell?

Name: Peter
Line: (gasping) This sucks!

Name: Brice
Line: Now, this is crafted from a reclaimed sub-Ultron arm straight from Sokovia. Here. You try.

Name: Aaron
Line: Man, I wanted something low-key. Why are you trying to upsell me, man?

Name: Brice
Line: Okay, okay, okay. I got what you need, all right? I got tons of great stuff here. One sec.

Name: Brice
Line: Okay, I got, uh, black hole grenades, Chitauri railguns...

Name: Schultz
Line: You letting off shots in public now? Hurry up. Look, times are changing. We’re the only ones selling these high tech weapons.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) Oh, this must be where the ATM robbers got their stuff.

Name: Aaron
Line: I need something to stick up somebody. I’m not trying to shoot them back in time.

Name: Brice
Line: I got anti-grav climbers.

Name: Aaron
Line: Yo, climbers?

Name: Brice
Line: Okay, what the hell was that?

Name: Schultz
Line: Did you set us up?

Name: Aaron
Line: Hey, hey, man.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey! Hey, come on. You gonna shoot at somebody, shoot at me.

Name: Schultz
Line: All right.

Name: Peter
Line: What was that?

Name: Peter
Line: What? Ah!

Name: Schultz
Line: We gotta call him.

Name: Brice
Line: No, no, no, no.

Name: Schultz
Line: Did you just do it again?

Name: Brice
Line: Shut up.

Name: Schultz
Line: I’m calling him.

Name: Mason
Line: Toomes’ phone.

Name: Mason
Line: Boss.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, my butt! Unh!

Name: Peter
Line: Great. Guess I’m gonna have to take a shortcut.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, guys. Good game. Have fun.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, hey, buddy. Sorry, no time to play. Here, go fetch.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoo! Now, this is more like it.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, whoa, whoa!

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa.

Name: Peter
Line: Smells really good!

Name: Peter
Line: Great movie!

Name: Peter
Line: Ugh... Oh, hey, guys.

Name: Peter
Line: No! No!

Name: Peter
Line: (on recording) Hey, it’s Peter. Leave a message.

Name: Ned
Line: (whispers) Peter, where are you? The hat’s not working. This is not cool.

Name: Peter
Line: Almost got you.

Name: Peter
Line: (panting) Thought you got away from me, didn’t you? I got you right where I want you.

Name: Peter
Line: Surprise!

Name: Peter
Line: What the hell?

Name: Peter
Line: Aahhhh!

Name: Peter
Line: Huh? Oh, hey.

Name: Peter
Line: And then he just, he just, like, swooped down like a monster and he picked me up and, uh, he took me up, like, a thousand feet and just dropped me. How’d you find me? Did you put a tracker in my suit or something?

Name: Tony
Line: I put everything in your suit. Including this heater.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa!

Name: Peter
Line: Whew, that’s better. Thanks.

Name: Tony
Line: What were you thinking?

Name: Peter
Line: The guy with the wings is obviously the source of the weapons. I gotta take him down.

Name: Tony
Line: Take him down now, huh? Steady, Crockett, there are people who handle this sort of thing.

Name: Peter
Line: The Avengers?

Name: Tony
Line: No, no, no. This is a little below their pay grade.

Name: Peter
Line: Anyway, Mr. Stark, you didn’t have to come all the way out here. I had that. I was fine.

Name: Tony
Line: Oh, I’m not here.

Name: Tony
Line: Thank God this place has Wi-Fi or you would be toast right now. Thank Ganesh while you’re at it.

Name: Tony
Line: Cheers.

Name: Tony
Line: Look, forget the flying vulture guy, please.

Name: Peter
Line: Why?

Name: Tony
Line: Why? Because I said so!

Name: Tony
Line: Sorry, I’m talking to a teenager. (to Peter) Stay close to the ground. Build up your game helping little people, like that lady that bought you the churro. Can’t you just be a friendly...

Name: Tony
Line: ...neighborhood Spider-Man?

Name: Peter
Line: But I’m ready for more than that now.

Name: Tony
Line: No, you are not.

Name: Peter
Line: That is not what you thought when I took on Captain America.

Name: Tony
Line: Trust me, kid. If Cap wanted to lay you out, he would’ve. Listen to me. If you come across these weapons again, call Happy.

Name: Peter
Line: Are you driving?

Name: Tony
Line: You know, it’s never too early to start thinking about college. I got some pull at MIT. (at his phone) End call.

Name: Peter
Line: No, I don’t need to go to col- Mr. Stark-

Name: Peter
Line: That’s awesome.

Name: Peter
Line: (mutters) Stay close to the ground? What is he talking about?

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, man, what’s up? I’m on my way back.

Name: Ned
Line: Actually, I was calling to say maybe you shouldn’t come. Listen to this.

Name: Flash
Line: When I say “penis,” you say “Parker.” Penis!

Name: Flash
Line: Penis!

Name: Ned
Line: Sorry, Peter. I guess we’re still losers. I’ll see you tomorrow.

Name: Peter
Line: I’ll see you tomorrow in school.

Name: Mason
Line: Whoa, whoa.

Name: Toomes
Line: Idiots. Idiots.

Name: Toomes
Line: Idiots!

Name: Mason
Line: Boss. Your wife keeps texting you. Something about a brake light?

Name: Toomes
Line: What’d I tell you about looking at my phone?

Name: Mason
Line: Oh, sorry. You left it out. You know I’m a curious person by nature.

Name: Mason
Line: I finished designing that high-altitude vacuum seal.

Name: Toomes
Line: Huh?

Name: Mason
Line: In case you want to, you know, go for the big one?

Name: Toomes
Line: You’re still on that? I told you, no. The answer’s no. Forget it.

Name: Brice
Line: Whoo!

Name: Brice
Line: I mean, that was badass.

Name: Toomes
Line: How many times have I told you not to fire them out in the open?

Name: Brice
Line: You said, move the merchandise.

Name: Toomes
Line: Under the radar. Under the radar! That’s how we survive. If you bring Damage Control or the Avengers down here, we’re through. You’re out there wearing that goofy thing, lightning up cars, calling yourself the Shocker. “I’m the Shocker. I shock people.” What is this, pro wrestling?

Name: Brice
Line: Ah, whatever, old man. Come on.

Name: Toomes
Line: Look, look. I know you don’t give a crap about anything. But I do. I built this whole place because I got people I have to look after.

Name: Brice
Line: (mockingly) Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

Name: Toomes
Line: You know what? I can’t afford your bullshit. Get out of here.

Name: Brice
Line: What?

Name: Toomes
Line: You’re done. You’re off the crew.

Name: Brice
Line: Yeah, all right. All right. Wonder if you can afford me out there, though, right? With everything I know.

Name: Toomes
Line: Excuse me?

Name: Brice
Line: Um, I’m just saying...

Name: Brice
Line: ...maybe your wife would like to know where you really get your money from.

Name: Toomes
Line: You know what?

Name: Brice
Line: What?

Name: Toomes
Line: You’re right. (to Mason, in a low voice) That work?

Name: Mason
Line: I don’t know.

Name: Toomes
Line: I can’t afford that.

Name: Schultz
Line: Damn.

Name: Toomes
Line: I thought this was the antigravity gun.

Name: Mason
Line: What? No, that’s that one.

Name: Toomes
Line: Here. Now you’re the Shocker. Go out there and find that weapon he lost.

Name: Schultz
Line: All right.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh.

Name: Ned
Line: Hey, thanks for bailing on me.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, well, something came up.

Name: Ned
Line: Oh, what is that?

Name: Peter
Line: I don’t know. Some guy tried to vaporize me with it.

Name: Ned
Line: Seriously?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah.

Name: Ned
Line: Awesome.

Name: Ned
Line: I mean, not awesome. Totally uncool of that guy. So scary.

Name: Peter
Line: Well, look, I think it’s a power source.

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah, but it’s connected to all these microprocessors. That’s an inductive charging plate. That’s what I use to charge my toothbrush.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoever’s making these weapons is obviously combining alien tech with ours.

Name: Ned
Line: That is literally the coolest sentence anyone has ever said. I just want to thank you for letting me be part of your journey into this amazing-

Name: Peter
Line: I gotta figure out what this thing is and who makes it.

Name: Ned
Line: We’ll go to the lab after class and run some tests.

Name: Peter
Line: Let’s do it.

Name: Ned
Line: First, I say we put the glowy thing in the mass spectrometer.

Name: Peter
Line: First, we gotta come up with a better name than “glowy thingy.”

Name: Ned
Line: You’re right.

Name: Peter
Line: Crap.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) Come on, come on, come on, come on, come on, come on.

Name: Schultz
Line: High schools creep me out.

Name: Schultz
Line: They got this funny smell, you know?

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, that’s one of the guys that tried to kill me.

Name: Ned
Line: What?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah.

Name: Ned
Line: We gotta get out of here.

Name: Peter
Line: No, no, no, no, no. I gotta follow them. Maybe they can lead me to the guy that dropped me in the lake.

Name: Ned
Line: Someone dropped you in a lake?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, it was not good.

Name: Ned
Line: (whispers) Peter-

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) No. Stay there, Ned.

Name: Ned
Line: (whispers) Peter.

Name: Ned
Line: (in a normal voice) Nothing.

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah. You good?

Name: Schultz
Line: It’s saying there was an energy pulse right here.

Name: Schultz
Line: So are we.

Name: Ned
Line: This is so awesome.

Name: Peter
Line: I know, right?

Name: Peter
Line: They’re in Brooklyn.

Name: Ned
Line: Staten Island.

Name: Ned
Line: Leaving Jersey.

Name: Ned
Line: They stopped.

Name: Peter
Line: Maryland?

Name: Ned
Line: What’s there?

Name: Peter
Line: I don’t know. Evil lair?

Name: Ned
Line: They have a lair?

Name: Peter
Line: Dude. A gang with alien guns run by a guy with wings? Yeah, they have a lair.

Name: Ned
Line: (nods) Badass. But how are you gonna get there if it’s, like, 300 miles away?

Name: Peter
Line: It’s not too far from D.C.

Name: Peter
Line: Guys.

Name: Liz
Line: Peter?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, I was hoping maybe I could rejoin the team.

Name: Flash
Line: No, no way. You can’t just quit on us, stroll up, and be welcomed back by everyone.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Hey, welcome back, Peter. Flash, you’re back to first alternate.

Name: Flash
Line: What?

Name: Michelle
Line: Excuse me, can we go already? ‘Cause I was hoping to get in some light protesting in front of one of the embassies before dinner, so.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Protesting is patriotic. Let’s get on the bus.

Name: Liz
Line: Focus up, everyone. Our next topic is the moons of Saturn.

Name: Flash
Line: Fort Sumter.

Name: Liz
Line: Okay, guys, let’s focus. Next one.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Liz, don’t overwork them.

Name: Peter
Line: Uh, strontium, barium, vibranium.

Name: Liz
Line: Very good, Peter. Glad to have you back.

Name: Peter
Line: Glad to be back.

Name: Liz
Line: What is the current standard unit of radioactive-

Name: Peter
Line: Can I take this real quick? I’ll only be a sec.

Name: Liz
Line: Yeah, fine.

Name: Peter
Line: Hello?

Name: Happy
Line: Got a blip on my screen here. You left New York?

Name: Liz
Line: Okay, focus up, everyone.

Name: Peter
Line: Tracker.

Name: Peter
Line: (in a normal voice) Uh, yeah. No, it’s just a school trip. It’s, uh, it’s nothing.

Name: Peter
Line: Look, Happy, I gotta say, you tracking me without my permission is a complete violation of my privacy.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) That’s different.

Name: Happy
Line: What’s different?

Name: Peter
Line: Nothing. Look, it’s just the Academic Decathlon. It’s no big deal.

Name: Happy
Line: Hey, hey. I’ll decide if it’s no big deal.

Name: Happy
Line: Sounds like it’s no big deal, but remember, I’m watching you.

Name: Liz
Line: Everyone stick together.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Yeah.

Name: Flash
Line: I’ve seen bigger.

Name: Peter
Line: (to Ned) Hey, you brought your laptop, right?

Name: Ned
Line: Why?

Name: Ned
Line: Peter, why are we removing the tracker from your suit?

Name: Peter
Line: Uh, because I gotta follow these guys to their boss before they move again and I don’t really want Mr. Stark to know about it.

Name: Ned
Line: So you’re lying to Iron Man now?

Name: Peter
Line: No, I’m not lying. He just doesn’t really get what I can do yet.

Name: Peter
Line: Ah... Gotcha.

Name: Peter
Line: All right, Happy. Enjoy tracking this lamp.

Name: Ned
Line: There’s a ton of other subsystems in here...

Name: Peter
Line: Hmm?

Name: Ned
Line: (smirks) ...but they’re all disabled by the Training Wheels Protocol.

Name: Peter
Line: What?

Name: Peter
Line: “Training Wheels Protocol?”

Name: Peter
Line: Turn it off.

Name: Ned
Line: I don’t think that’s a good idea. I mean, they’re probably blocked for a reason.

Name: Peter
Line: Come on, man. I don’t need training wheels.

Name: Peter
Line: I’m sick of him treating me like a kid all the time. It’s not cool.

Name: Ned
Line: But you are a kid.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, a kid who can stop a bus with his bare hands.

Name: Ned
Line: Peter, I just don’t think this is a great idea. I mean, what if this is illegal?

Name: Peter
Line: Look, please. This is my chance to prove myself. I can handle it. Ned, come on.

Name: Ned
Line: I really don’t think this is a good idea.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) The guy in the chair.

Name: Ned
Line: Don’t do that.

Name: Peter
Line: Come on.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, the glowy thing, it’s evidence. Keep it safe.

Name: Peter
Line: All right?

Name: Ned
Line: Okay, okay.

Name: Peter
Line: They’re moving.

Name: Ned
Line: Be careful.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Liz.

Name: Liz
Line: (whispers) Perfect timing. We’re gonna go swimming. Come on, come on, come on.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) What?

Name: Peter
Line: Hey!

Name: Peter
Line: I was, uh... I was gonna go study, um, in the business center.

Name: Liz
Line: Peter, you don’t need to study. You’re, like, the smartest guy I’ve ever met.

Name: Liz
Line: And besides... Um, a rebellious group activity the day before competition is good for morale.

Name: Peter
Line: Hmm?

Name: Liz
Line: Um, well, I read that in a TED Talk, so, I-I heard it in a TED Talk. And I read a coaching book.

Name: Peter
Line: Wow, you really... This is really important to you.

Name: Liz
Line: Yeah. It’s our future. I’m not gonna screw it up. Besides, we raided the minibar and these candy bars were, like, eleven dollars. So get your trunks on and come on.

Name: Liz
Line: I’m coming, I’m coming.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Good evening, Peter.

Name: Peter
Line: Hello? Hello?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Congratulations on completing the rigorous Training Wheels Protocol and gaining access to your suit’s full capabilities.

Name: Peter
Line: Ah, thank you.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: So where would you like to take me tonight?

Name: Peter
Line: (stuttering) S, I, I, put a tracker on someone. He’s a bad guy.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Tracker located.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Plotting course to intercept target.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay, well, as long as I make it back in time for Decathlon, it’s fine.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: One hundred meters from destination and closing.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Jump now.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Detecting three individuals.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) Why is their secret lair in a gas station? That’s so lame.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, suit lady, what are they doing?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Do you want to hear what they’re saying?

Name: Peter
Line: I can hear what they’re saying? Uh, yeah.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Activating Enhanced Reconnaissance Mode.

Name: Mason
Line: I got the gauntlet from the Lagos cleanup. The rest is all my design.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, that’s so cool.

Name: Schultz
Line: I love it. They keep making messes, we keep getting rich.

Name: Mason
Line: Target inbound.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, they’re in the middle of a heist. I could catch them all red-handed. This is awesome. Okay, I’m gonna get a little closer so I can see what’s happening.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Would you like me to engage Enhanced Combat Mode?

Name: Peter
Line: Uh, Enhanced Combat Mode? Yeah.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Activating Instant Kill.

Name: Peter
Line: No, no, no, no, no, no, no. I don’t want to kill anybody!

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Deactivating Instant Kill.

Name: Schultz
Line: Did you hear that?

Name: Peter
Line: What the hell just happened? What was that?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You jumped off the sign and landed on your face.

Name: Peter
Line: Suit lady, what’s wrong with my web-shooters?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Rapid-fire is the default for Enhanced Combat Mode.

Name: Peter
Line: Why would I need rapid-fire?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Would you like to see more options?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You have 576 possible web-shooter combinations.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, Mr. Stark really overdid it.

Name: Schultz
Line: You two wait right here.

Name: Mason
Line: Wait. You’re gonna want to turn on the dampers, though, or that thing will shatter your arm.

Name: Schultz
Line: All right. Where’s the dampers?

Name: Peter
Line: That one.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Great choice.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Would you like me to set this as your new default?

Name: Peter
Line: No, no, no.

Name: Mason
Line: Push that in.

Name: Schultz
Line: Right here?

Name: Mason
Line: No, no, the other-

Name: Schultz
Line: This one right here?

Name: Mason
Line: Yeah, push. [Peter runs behind the gas station, away from the truck, and leaps on some trucks to reach the roof of the building.]

Name: Peter
Line: What was that?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Taser webs.

Name: Peter
Line: Taser webs? I don’t want taser webs.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You seem to be very unfamiliar with your web-shooter settings. Would you like to run a refresher course?

Name: Peter
Line: No, just... You choose.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Sure thing.

Name: Schultz
Line: I have visual.

Name: Mason
Line: Green light, green light.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, that’s him.

Name: Mason
Line: Deploy anchors.

Name: Mason
Line: No outgoing distress signals. You’re all clear.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, cool. It’s some kind of matter phase shifter.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Big Bird! This doesn’t belong to you!

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, god.

Name: Peter
Line: Suit lady, what was that?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You told me to choose.

Name: Peter
Line: What? No, just set everything back to normal.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: Activating all systems.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, my head.

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You appear to have a mild concussion.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, so where am I right now?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: I’m not sure. The container walls are hindering my sensors.

Name: Peter
Line: Wait a minute. They must have hijacked the truck and taken me to their evil lair. Okay, suit lady. We’re gonna have to fight our way out of this one.

Name: Peter
Line: Three, two, one!

Name: Peter
Line: What is this place? Suit lady, where am I?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You’re in the most secure facility on the Eastern Seaboard. The Damage Control Deep Storage Vault.

Name: Peter
Line: No. Seriously?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: The door will most likely remain closed until morning.

Name: Peter
Line: (disappointed) Morning?

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, suit lady, I kind of feel bad calling you “suit lady,” you know? I think I should probably give you a name... like Liz. No, no, no. God, that’s... that’s weird.

Name: Peter
Line: What about Karen?

Name: Suit Lady
Line: You can call me Karen if you would like.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Karen, what else can this suit do?

Name: Peter
Line: What?

Name: Peter
Line: Maybe we should run that refresher course.

Name: Karen
Line: Ricochet web.

Name: Peter
Line: Ricochet web.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa! Cool.

Name: Karen
Line: Splitter web.

Name: Karen
Line: Web grenade.

Name: Peter
Line: Web grenade!

Name: Peter
Line: Should I tell Liz that I’m Spider-Man?

Name: Karen
Line: Who is Liz?

Name: Peter
Line: Who is Liz? She’s.. heh. She’s the best. She’s awesome. She, uh, she’s just a girl who goes to my school. And, uh... Yeah, I just... I really want to tell her, but it’s kind of weird, you know? “Hey, I’m... I’m Spider-Man.”

Name: Karen
Line: What’s weird about that?

Name: Peter
Line: What if she’s expecting someone like Tony Stark? I mean, imagine how disappointed she’d be when she sees me.

Name: Karen
Line: Well, if I were her, I wouldn’t be disappointed at all.

Name: Peter
Line: Thanks, Karen. It’s really nice to have somebody to talk to. Hey, how long we been here anyways?

Name: Karen
Line: Thirty seven minutes.

Name: Peter
Line: What? Thirty seven minutes?

Name: Peter
Line: That’s insane. I cannot take this anymore. I gotta... I gotta get out of here.

Name: Peter
Line: There’s got to be something in here I can use.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay, let’s see.

Name: Peter
Line: Nope.

Name: Peter
Line: That’s awesome. [The Ultron head makes a clanging sound as it is discarded on the floor. Peter holds a purple glowing object.]

Name: Peter
Line: Ah, hey, it’s like the glowy thing.

Name: Karen
Line: That glowy thing is an explosive Chitauri energy core.

Name: Peter
Line: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! You mean, we’ve been carrying around a bomb?

Name: Karen
Line: It would require radiation to transform it into an explosive state.

Name: Peter
Line: No, no, no, no, no.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey! Please! Please, somebody, let me out! Hey! Karen, you have to help me override that time lock.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay Karen. Lower the voltage and run it.

Name: Karen
Line: Trial unsuccessful.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay, we’re just gonna have to try every sequence.

Name: Ned
Line: Okay, hold on, hold on.

Name: Karen
Line: Initiating trial 247.

Name: Peter
Line: It worked! It works!

Name: Peter
Line: Karen, you have to get me to Decathlon as fast as possible.

Name: Karen
Line: Sure thing. Just tell me where it is.

Name: Peter
Line: Right across the street from the Washington Monument.

Name: Ned
Line: Hey, it’s Ned. Leave a message.

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, call me back! The glowy thing is a bomb!

Name: Karen
Line: There’s a vehicle approaching on your right.

Name: Michelle
Line: Zero.

Name: Liz
Line: You guys, I am so proud of you.

Name: Flash
Line: Told you we didn’t need Peter.

Name: Ned
Line: Flash, you didn’t answer a single question.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Taking it all in, Michelle?

Name: Michelle
Line: Oh, yeah, I just... um, I don’t really want to celebrate something that was built by slaves.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Oh, I’m sure the Washington Monument wasn’t built by-

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Okay. Enjoy your book.

Name: Michelle
Line: Thanks.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, Ned, you’re alive!

Name: Ned
Line: (whispers) Peter, are you okay?

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, Ned, where’s the glowy thing, the glowy thing?

Name: Ned
Line: Don’t worry, it’s safe. It’s in my backpack.

Name: Peter
Line: No, Ned, listen! No, no, Ned, the glowy thing is dangerous.

Name: Ned
Line: You missed the Decathlon. I covered for you.

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, listen to me!

Name: Ned
Line: We’re at the Washington Monument now. You gotta- [Liz takes the phone from Ned.]

Name: Liz
Line: Peter, is that you?

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, hey, Liz.

Name: Karen
Line: Is that Liz?

Name: Peter
Line: Please put Ned back on the phone.

Name: Karen
Line: You should tell her how you feel.

Name: Liz
Line: You freak! You are so lucky we won. You know, I want to be mad, but I’m more worried. Like, what is going on with you?

Name: Peter
Line: Liz, I have to talk to Ned. It’s really important!

Name: Peter

Name: Peter
Line: Yes! Ned, the guy with the wings is Liz’s dad.

Name: Ned
Line: What?

Name: Peter
Line: I know. I gotta tell Mr. Stark. Call Happy Hogan. He’s Mr. Stark’s head of security. And, uh, get a computer to track my phone for me.

Name: Ned
Line: Are you gonna be okay?

Name: Peter
Line: Hurry, we gotta catch him before he leaves town.

Name: Flash
Line: I’m sorry about dinner, but I know when branzino’s fresh, and that was not fresh, okay? So...

Name: Peter
Line: (in a gravelly voice) Flash, I need your car and your phone.

Name: Flash
Line: Uh, sir, technically, this is my dad’s car, sir. So I can’t...

Name: Peter
Line: (in a normal voice) Hello, Ned? Hey, hey, hey, hey, can you hear me?

Name: Ned
Line: Go for Ned.

Name: Peter
Line: Ned, I need you to track my phone for me.

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah, but where is it?

Name: Ned
Line: Genius move. Okay, he just passed the GameStop on Jackson Avenue.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, where are the headlights on this thing? I’m in Flash’s car.

Name: Ned
Line: I’ll pull the specs.

Name: Peter
Line: Okay, you’re on speakerphone.

Name: Ned
Line: You stole Flash’s car. Awesome.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, it’s awesome. It’s awe... Whoa!

Name: Peter
Line: Get out of the way, get out of the way! Move! Move!

Name: Ned
Line: Peter, are you okay?

Name: Peter
Line: I’ve never really driven before. Only with May in parking lots. This is a huge step up...

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, have you gotten through to Happy yet?

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah. I’m working on it. I just gotta backdoor the phone system.

Name: Ned
Line: Guy in the chair.

Name: Happy
Line: Takeoff in nine minutes. (to Ned) Hello? Hello? Who is this?

Name: Ned
Line: Uh... Mr. Happy, it’s Ned.

Name: Happy
Line: Who?

Name: Ned
Line: I’m an associate of Peter Parker. Got something very important to tell you-

Name: Happy
Line: You gotta be shitting me.

Name: Ned
Line: Damn.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Ned, how we coming on with those headlights?

Name: Ned
Line: Uh... Round knob to the left of the steering wheel, turn clockwise.

Name: Peter
Line: Left. Okay. Okay, perfect. So where’s my phone now?

Name: Ned
Line: Um... He stopped in an old industrial park in Brooklyn.

Name: Peter
Line: What? That makes no sense. I thought he said he was going out of town!

Name: Ned
Line: Weird. Oh, I reached Mr. Happy. Don’t think he likes you, by the way. It sounded like he was catching a flight. He said something about taking off in nine minutes.

Name: Peter
Line: What?

Name: Ned
Line: He was surrounded by a bunch of boxes.

Name: Peter
Line: Boxes? It’s moving day. It’s moving day! It’s moving day! He’s gonna rob that plane! I gotta stop him!

Name: Happy
Line: All right, wheels up in eight minutes. We just got to load Tony’s old Hulkbuster armor, prototype for Cap’s new shield, and the Meging... the Meg... the... Thor’s magic belt.

Name: Ned
Line: Okay, slow down. You’re getting close. It’s on your right.

Name: Peter
Line: What?

Name: Ned
Line: Turn right! Turn right!

Name: Ned
Line: Peter, are you okay?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah. Just keep trying to get through to Happy.

Name: Ned
Line: It’s been an honor, Spider-Man.

Name: Ned
Line: Uh...

Name: Ned
Line: (awkwardly) I’m... looking... at... porn.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey! Surprised?

Name: Toomes
Line: Oh, hey, Pete. I didn’t hear you come in.

Name: Peter
Line: It’s over. I’ve got you.

Name: Toomes
Line: You know, I gotta tell you, Pete, I really, really admire your grit. I see why Liz likes you. I do. When you first came to the house, I wasn’t sure. I thought, “Really?” But I get it now.

Name: Peter
Line: How could you do this to her?

Name: Toomes
Line: To her? I’m not doing anything to her, Pete. I’m doing this for her.

Name: Peter
Line: Huh, yeah.

Name: Toomes
Line: (sighs) Peter, you’re young. You don’t understand how the world works.

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, but I understand that selling weapons to criminals is wrong.

Name: Toomes
Line: How do you think your buddy Stark paid for that tower? Or any of his little toys? Those people, Pete, those people up there, the rich and the powerful, they do whatever they want. Guys like us, like you and me, they don’t care about us. We build their roads and we fight all their wars and everything, but they don’t care about us. We have to pick up after ‘em. We have to eat their table scraps. That’s how it is. I know you know what I’m talking about, Peter.

Name: Peter
Line: Why are you telling me this?

Name: Toomes
Line: Because I want you to understand. And... I needed a little time to get her airborne.

Name: Toomes
Line: I’m sorry, Peter.

Name: Peter
Line: What are you talking about? That thing hasn’t even touched me yet.

Name: Toomes
Line: True. Then again, wasn’t really trying to.

Name: Mason
Line: Chief, they’re powering up engines.

Name: Toomes
Line: Okay.

Name: Mason
Line: Come on, come on, come on.

Name: Toomes
Line: Yeah, yeah.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, god. Okay, ready?

Name: Peter
Line: Hello! Hello! Please. Hey, hey, please. I’m down here. I’m down here. I’m stuck. I’m stuck. I can’t move. I can’t...

Name: Tony
Line: If you’re nothing without this suit, then you shouldn’t have it.

Name: Peter
Line: Come on, Peter. Come on, Spider-Man. Come on, Spider-Man. Come on, Spider-Man. Come on, Spider-Man!

Name: Mason
Line: Launch for intercept. Green light. Green light.

Name: Toomes
Line: Oh, yeah.

Name: Toomes
Line: Got a visual on the plane, feeling a little resistance.

Name: Mason
Line: It’s probably just a drag on the new turbines.

Name: Peter
Line: Ah! Whoa!

Name: Mason
Line: Look out for the cloaking cameras. Stay in the blind spots.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, my god! Oh, my god!

Name: Mason
Line: Deploy high-altitude vacuum seal.

Name: Toomes
Line: This better work, Mason.

Name: Mason
Line: Trust me, boss. Even one of those boxes and we are set for life.

Name: Toomes
Line: Yeah.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey! Ah! Whew.

Name: Mason
Line: You have thirty seconds to get to the cockpit and override their security.

Name: Toomes
Line: Cloning transponder signal.

Name: Mason
Line: Launching decoy drone.

Name: Toomes
Line: Entering new coordinates.

Name: Happy
Line: Good, so it’s on its way?

Name: Happy
Line: Okay, thank you. All right.

Name: Toomes
Line: Hot dog.

Name: Peter
Line: Just a typical homecoming on the outside of an invisible jet... Fighting my girlfriend’s dad.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, god!

Name: Peter
Line: Whew. I can’t believe that worked.

Name: Mason
Line: Chief, chief, they’re losing altitude. Get out of there.

Name: Toomes
Line: I’m not going home empty-handed.

Name: Peter
Line: Oh, my god.

Name: Mason
Line: Get out of there! What are you doing?

Name: Peter
Line: Please turn! Please turn!

Name: Toomes
Line: Hey, Pedro.

Name: Toomes
Line: Bingo.

Name: Peter
Line: Your wing suit. Your wing suit’s gonna explode!

Name: Toomes
Line: Time to go home, Pete.

Name: Peter
Line: I’m trying to save you!

Name: Peter
Line: No.

Name: Ned
Line: It looked so insane. That whole... Like, it was just crazy. He, he was just like, “Zzzz,” and you were like, “Ah!”

Name: Peter
Line: Shh.

Name: Ned
Line: And then I just hit him with the “pew.” It was so, oh, my god.

Name: Peter
Line: You saved me. It was awesome.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Liz!

Name: Liz
Line: Bye.

Name: Peter
Line: Liz.

Name: Peter
Line: Liz, look. I’m so sorry.

Name: Liz
Line: You say that a lot. What are you sorry for this time?

Name: Liz
Line: The dance? That was a pretty crappy thing to do.

Name: Peter
Line: Well, yeah, but I... I mean, your dad... I can’t imagine what you’re going through. If there’s anything I can do to help...

Name: Liz
Line: (fighting tears) I guess we’re moving to Oregon. Mom says it’s nice there, so that’s cool. Anyways, Dad doesn’t want us here during the trial, so...

Name: Peter
Line: Liz, I... I...

Name: Liz
Line: Bye, Peter. Whatever’s going on with you, I hope you figure it out.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: Congratulations, Decathlon national champions.

Name: Mr. Harrington
Line: I’m gonna have to put this back in the trophy case soon, but just for motivation right now at this practice. I’m a little ahead of the game, but we will need a new team captain next year. So I’m appointing Michelle.

Name: Michelle
Line: Uh, thank you. My friends call me M.J.

Name: Ned
Line: I thought you didn’t have any friends.

Name: Michelle
Line: I didn’t.

Name: Peter
Line: I... I gotta go.

Name: Michelle
Line: Hey, where you going?

Name: Michelle
Line: What are you hiding, Peter?

Name: Michelle
Line: I’m just kidding. I don’t care. Bye. (to Decathlon team) All right, so we should run some drills.

Name: Ned
Line: Yeah.

Name: Peter
Line: Hey, Happy. What, uh... What are you doing here?

Name: Happy
Line: I really owe you one. I don’t know what I would do without this job. I mean, before I met Tony-

Name: Peter
Line: So, uh, how long you been here?

Name: Happy
Line: Long enough to be awkward. Boss wants to see you.

Name: Peter
Line: (whispers) Is he here too?

Name: Happy
Line: In the toilet? No, he’s upstate.

Name: Peter
Line: Upstate? Like, upstate-upstate?

Name: Happy
Line: Yeah, let’s go.

Name: Happy
Line: Take a look. It’s pretty impressive, huh?

Name: Happy
Line: They just finished remodeling the whole thing.

Name: Happy
Line: You don’t see that every day.

Name: Tony
Line: Oh, there they are. How was the ride up?

Name: Happy
Line: Good.

Name: Tony
Line: Give me a minute with the kid.

Name: Happy
Line: Seriously?

Name: Tony
Line: Yeah. I gotta talk to the kid.

Name: Happy
Line: I’ll be close behind.

Name: Tony
Line: How about a loose follow? All right? Boundaries are good.

Name: Tony
Line: Sorry I took your suit. I mean, you had it coming. Actually, it turns out it was the perfect sort of tough-love moment that you needed, right? To urge you on, right? Wouldn’t you think? Don’t you think?

Name: Peter
Line: Yeah, yeah, I guess.

Name: Tony
Line: Let’s just say it was.

Name: Peter
Line: Mr. Stark, I really-

Name: Tony
Line: You screwed the pooch hard. Big time. But then you did the right thing. Took the dog to the free clinic, you raised the hybrid puppies... All right, not my best analogy. (beat) I was wrong about you. I think, with a little more mentoring, you could be a real asset to the team.

Name: Peter
Line: To the... To the team?

Name: Tony
Line: Yeah. Anyway... (points at a door) There’s about fifty reporters behind that door. Real ones, not bloggers.

Name: Tony
Line: When you’re ready... Why don’t you try that on? And I’ll introduce the world to the newest official member of the Avengers

Name: Tony
Line: Yeah. Give that a look.

Name: Tony
Line: So, after the press conference, Happy will show you to your room, your new quarters. (to Happy) Where’s he between? He’s next to Vision?

Name: Happy
Line: Yeah, Vision’s not big on doors.

Name: Tony
Line: It’s fun.

Name: Happy
Line: Or walls.

Name: Tony
Line: (to Peter) You’ll fit right in.

Name: Peter
Line: Thank you, Mr. Stark. But I’m good.

Name: Tony
Line: You’re good? Good? How are you good?

Name: Peter
Line: Well, I mean, I’m... I’d rather just stay on the ground for a little while. Friendly neighborhood Spider-Man. Somebody’s got to look out for the little guy, right?

Name: Tony
Line: You turning me down? You better think about this. (pointing at the new Spider-Man suit) Look at that. Look at me. Last chance, yes or no?

Name: Peter
Line: No.

Name: Tony
Line: Okay. It’s kind of a Springsteen-y, working class hero vibe that I dig. Uh, Happy will take you home. Yeah?

Name: Happy
Line: Yeah. (to Peter) Mind waiting in the car? I need a minute.

Name: Peter
Line: Thank you, Mr. Stark.

Name: Tony
Line: Yes, Mr. Parker. Very well.

Name: Peter
Line: See you around.

Name: Tony
Line: Okay.

Name: Peter
Line: That was a test, right? There’s, uh, nobody back there?

Name: Tony
Line: Yes, you passed. All right, skedaddle there, young buck.

Name: Peter
Line: Thank you, Mr. Stark. Thank you.

Name: Tony
Line: Yeah, thank you.

Name: Happy
Line: Told you he’s a good kid.

Name: Happy
Line: He left.

Name: Tony
Line: You know what? He actually made a really mature choice. It just surprised the heck out of us.

Name: Tony
Line: (points at Happy) He told the kid to go wait in the car.

Name: Tony
Line: Think of something. How about, um... Hap, you still got that ring?

Name: Happy
Line: Do I... I, uh...

Name: Tony
Line: The engagement ring?

Name: Happy
Line: Are you kidding? I’ve been carrying this since 2008.

Name: Tony
Line: Okay.

Name: Tony
Line: Well, it would buy us a little time.

Name: Tony
Line: Like we need time.

Name: Tony
Line: Want me to get the door for you, hon?

Name: Peter
Line: Aunt May, did you do dinner already?

Name: Peter
Line: May?

Name: May
Line: What the fu...?

Name: Toomes
Line: If I knew who he was, he’d already be dead.
